snippet.textDisplay: I am skeptical about putting this up to an f-150. Due to gear reduction in a truck from the transmission the wheel torque can be much higher than the engine. Now I don't know the gearing on the 1:2 cybertruck but engine or motor torque is just the tip of how much power goes out the wheels. The gearing, differentials, wheel size, and traction all play an important part in determining how much power makes it to the ground. If the 1:2 cybertruck is direct drive it will be beat in terms of power because the ford 10 speed 1st gear ratio of 4.69:1 will give it technically 1,876lb-ft at the wheel shaft if the differentials were 1:1 (its not) this beats the motors combined 626lb-ft. The hacksmith can work this out using the gearing on their 1:2 cybertruck and comparing it. For the moment I question its ability to win. Let me know what you think. Pls don't go calling me a cybertruck and hacksmith hater. I love them. If i'm wrong with my estimates (I know the engine power isn't instant don't bother me about that) let me know.
